This paper deals with security and privacy issues in the Tor network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The analysis of RSA keys involves network infrastructure and cryptography, which could also be classified under networked systems (cs.NI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The identification of malicious relays and their attempts to attack onion services involves information theory (cs.IT) and software engineering (cs.SE).
